The paper deals with a cross-layer approach to random access that combines physical-layer network coding (PLNC) with multiuser detection (MUD). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents simulation results for performance measures such as throughput, packet loss rate, and energy efficiency, which suggests that it could also belong to the Signal Processing (cs.SI), Multimedia (cs.MM), or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
